{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was flying the liaison planes by then, which was for artillery spotting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was basically for the eyes of the big guns.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We would pick targets and find enemy-- that's what we were training now to do in Europe.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "All this training in-- in process of our training, we were told by people who had come back from combat that the Germans would not shoot at these little airplanes because you had a battalion of field artillery that you could get on them in about two seconds.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you could have 12 105 Howitzers on a target in about-- less than 10 seconds.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they would never shoot at you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's what we were told.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Didn't turn out to be the case, but that's what we were told.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Still, pursuing my dream of becoming a cadet in the air corps, Army Air Corps, I began to realize that it wouldn't be too long until this unit was going to go into combat overseas.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because some of the-- our sister units had left already and were in Europe, the ones that were trained, had train with us in Camp Adair.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This 104th division, the 96th division, and these fellows had already-- were already over there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So an opportunity came for me to-- to go to the parachute school at Fort Benning, Georgia, which is at Columbus.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this is an old military post, and not a-- and not a very nice place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was one of the-- one of the most difficult things, maybe with the possible exception of the Louisiana maneuvers, that I endured in the States in training.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The summer-- hot, miserable, tough like the-- the commandos.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everybody was-- rank didn't mean-- I was a staff sergeant.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Rank didn't mean a thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Majors, colonels, lieutenants, sergeant-- didn't matter.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
